```latex
\textbf{Associations between ACTL8 expression and the DSS in different clinical subgroups of UCEC.}
(A) Race: White; (B1) Clinical stage: Stage I; (B2) Clinical stage: Stage III; (C) Primary therapy outcome: CR;
(D1) Age: $\leq 60$; (D2) Age: $>60$; (E) Body mass index (BMI): $>30$; (F) Histological type: Endometrioid;
(G) Residual tumor: no residual tumor (R0); (H) Histologic grade: G3; (I1) Tumor invasion (\%): $<50$;
(I2) Tumor invasion (\%): $\geq 50$; (J) Menopause status: Post; (K1) Diabetes: No; (K2) Diabetes: Yes;
(L) Hormone therapy: No; (M1) Radiation therapy: No; (M2) Radiation therapy: Yes; (N) Weight: $>80$;
(O1) Height: $\leq 160$; (O2) Height: $>160$. All $p$ values were less than 0.05.
```

```latex
\textbf{Associations between ACTL8 expression and the PFI in different clinical subgroups of UCEC.}
(A) Race: White; (B1) Clinical stage: Stage I; (B2) Clinical stage: Stage III; (C) Primary therapy outcome: CR;
(D1) Age: $\leq 60$; (D2) Age: $>60$; (E) Body mass index (BMI): $>30$; (F) Histological type: Endometrioid;
(G) Residual tumor: no residual tumor (R0); (H1) Histologic grade: G2; (H2) Histologic grade: G3;
(I1) Tumor invasion (\%): $<50$; (I2) Tumor invasion (\%): $\geq 50$; (J) Menopause status: Post;
(K1) Diabetes: No; (K2) Diabetes: Yes; (L) Hormone therapy: No; (M) Radiation therapy: No;
(N) Weight: $>80$; (O1) Height: $\leq 160$; (O2) Height: $>160$.
All $p$ values were less than 0.05.
```

```latex
\textbf{ACTL8's co-expressed genes and interacting proteins.}
(A) Volcano plot obtained from the LinkedOmics database showing ACTL8's co-expressed genes tested by Pearson's correlation test in the UCEC cohort;
(B) protein--protein interaction network of ACTL8 obtained from the STRING online tool;
(C) Venn diagram showing the intersection between ACTL8 co-expressed genes and ACTL8-interacting proteins.
```

```latex
\textbf{ACTL8's positively and negatively co-expressed genes in UCEC analyzed by the LinkedOmics database.}
(A, C) The top 50 negatively co-expressed (A) and positively co-expressed (C) genes of ACTL8 are shown in heat maps;
(B, D) the top 12 negatively co-expressed (B) and positively co-expressed (D) genes of ACTL8 are shown in scatter plots.
A $p$ value of less than 0.05 was considered statistically significant.
```

```latex
\textbf{ACTL8's gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA) in the UCEC cohort analyzed by the LinkedOmics database.}
(A) Bar chart of ACTL8 gene ontology biological process (GO\_BP) enrichment;
(B) bar chart of ACTL8 gene ontology cellular component (GO\_CC) enrichment;
(C) bar chart of ACTL8 gene ontology molecular function (GO\_MF) enrichment;
(D) bar chart of ACTL8 Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes (KEGG) pathway enrichment.
(E) Biological Process, Cellular Component, and Molecular Function categories are represented by red, blue, and green bars, respectively.
Bar height indicates the number of IDs in both the user list and the category.
An FDR $\leq 0.05$ was considered statistically significant.
```
